# =============================================================================
# Basaa AUDIO-GROUNDED sample treebank — SUD
# The 10 individually-aligned sentences from Makasso & Lee (2015), each linked to
# its WAV in ../recordings/aligned/. Shared frame:
#     m-aange(1-child, subj)  a-N-verb(root; concord a- BOUND, NounClass on verb)  (OBJ comp:obj)
# Tokenization: the preverbal subject-concord is BOUND as the verb prefix a-
#   (NounClass=Bantu1 on the verb), per the agreed policy — rules/parsing.md PA-2
#   option (b). The spaced practical spelling is preserved in '# text_practical'.
# Tense FEAT is from the translation; nasal-tone is NOT the established tense
#   exponent (see ../glossary/transcription_and_gloss_review.md §4; rules/glossing.md GL-4).
# FORM = practical (toneless) normalization; MISC Ipa= the recovered IPA; verify vs audio.
# =============================================================================

# sent_id = bas_s01
# audio = ../recordings/aligned/bas_s01_child_speaks_basaa.wav
# text = maange amporo Basaa
# text_practical = maange a mporo Basaa
# text_eng = The child speaks Basaa.
1	maange	maange	NOUN	_	NounClass=Bantu1|Number=Sing	2	subj	_	Gloss=1-child|Morph=m-aange|Ipa=maàŋgɛ́
2	amporo	poro	VERB	_	NounClass=Bantu1|Tense=Pres|VerbForm=Fin	0	root	_	Gloss=1.AGR-PRS-speak|Morph=a-m-poro|NasalTone=H(obs)
3	Basaa	basaa	PROPN	_	_	2	comp:obj	_	Gloss=Basaa

